<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="254" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="13.[810,1457,1332,1709]" pageId="13" pageNumber="254">
We have not found a specimen in P or in another herbarium representing this taxon. The protologue describes a tree 
<quantity box="[1366,1455,1395,1422]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.25" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="254" unit="m" value="32.5" valueMax="35.0" valueMin="30.0">30-35 m</quantity>
tall, with a 
<quantity box="[930,1034,1427,1454]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="254" unit="cm" value="50.0" valueMax="60.0" valueMin="40.0">40-60 cm</quantity>
wide trunk. Moreover is indicated that it has the same wood characteristics as 
<emphasis box="[1208,1454,1459,1485]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="254">
<taxonomicName box="[1208,1451,1459,1485]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lythraceae" genus="Lagerstroemia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="13" pageNumber="254" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="petiolaris">Lagerstroemia petiolaris</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
We received the following additional information from Thierry Deroin (P): “in the Louis Pierre’s slide library at P, are kept 4 slides of 
<taxonomicName box="[1028,1209,1555,1581]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lythraceae" genus="Lagerstroemia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="13" pageNumber="254" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1028,1172,1555,1580]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="254">Lagerstroemia</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
(2 for wood anatomy, 1 for petiole, 1 for lamina), associated with an envelope with rough anatomical sketches and a reference to ‘ 
<emphasis box="[1322,1448,1618,1644]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="254">Pierre 1819</emphasis>
’ (possibly a specimen?). In the general collection, however, the latter is not present”.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
